  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Biomarkers of bone resorption will be measured in the blood of patients with bone metastases
      from prostate cancer during the course of their illness. Changes in these biomarkers will be
      correlated with the patient's treatment with antiandrogen therapy and bisphosphonates and the
      response and/or progression of their cancer. It is hoped that serial measurement of these
      biomarkers may allow therapeutic monitoring in the future with successful individualisation
      of bisphosphonate therapy for metastatic prostate cancer.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
